author: Australian Associated Press
title: RBA unveils new $10 notes, celebrates Australian writers | Daily Mail Online
text: Share There's also images of yellow bramble wattle and a sulphur-crested cockatoo. The faces of famous Australian writers Dame Mary Gilmore and AB 'Banjo' Paterson remain on each side, along with microprint excerpts of their writings. OLD: There's believed to be about 120 million $10 notes already in circulation OLD: 'The existing series of banknotes can continue to be used as all previously issued banknotes remain legal tender,' RBA said Tactile features of two raised dots will be added to the new bills to help the vision-impaired distinguish between banknote denominations. There's believed to be about 120 million $10 notes already in circulation. In a statement, the RBA said it may take some time for the new bills to be circulated widely. 'The existing series of banknotes can continue to be used as all previously issued banknotes remain legal tender,' the statement said. The design of the new $10 banknote is pictured. The new bills will be distributed in September The next $10 dollar bank note has been revealed by the Reserve Bank of Australia Share or comment on this article 672
